# Cloudflare Pages header overrides (staged into dist/ by `npm run deploy`).
#
# Pages' default is Cache-Control: max-age=14400 — browsers then serve
# every asset from their HTTP cache for 4 hours, so a fresh deploy doesn't
# reach returning players (and even the service worker's network-first
# fetches were answered stale before sw.js switched to cache: 'no-cache').
# Force revalidation instead: files are still cached, but each request
# checks the ETag and unchanged files cost a 304.
/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
